---
/**
 * Work Page — Layer 1
 * Tiered repo showcase: Hero (2) + Shipped (5) + Cooking (2+2 books).
 * SPAR verdict: Curate on site, don't censor on GitHub.
 */
import "../styles/global.css";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import TamilRoot from "../components/TamilRoot.astro";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Work | Naveen Riaz</title>
    <meta name="description" content="What I build. Papers, open source tools, and books. Honesty over impressiveness." />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  </head>
  <body class="section-work">
    <Header activeNav="work" />

    <main class="container container--narrow">
      <section class="page-hero section">
        <h1>Work</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">What I build.</p>
        <p>
          I organise my work in three layers. What my body has shipped.
          What my mind is cooking. What my soul is exploring. Every tool
          here serves one belief: living systems thrive when their decisions improve.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Body: Shipped -->
      <section class="section--tight">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <span class="glow-dot" style="color: var(--body-color);"></span>
          <h2>Body <span class="layer-label">Shipped</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-grid">
          <div class="hero-card">
            <h3>SPAR-Kit</h3>
            <p class="work-type">Open Source CLI</p>
            <p>Run structured AI debates in your terminal. Multiple personas argue, a critic stress-tests, an arbiter synthesises. The friction is the feature.</p>
            <a href="https://github.com/synthanai/spar-kit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub →</a>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-card">
            <h3>Intent of Thought</h3>
            <p class="work-type">Academic Paper</p>
            <p>GPS for AI reasoning. A framework where AI declares its thinking strategy before generating, the same way a GPS announces your route before you drive.</p>
            <div class="link-row">
              <a href="https://github.com/synthanai/intent-of-thought/blob/main/paper/intent_of_thought.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the Paper →</a>
              <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18836659" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="link-secondary">Zenodo DOI →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="shipped-grid">
          <a href="https://github.com/synthanai/decision-moment-graph" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="shipped-card">
            <h4>Decision Moment Graph</h4>
            <p>Open standard for decision governance. Stop storing chats, store decision objects.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="https://github.com/synthanai/ramp-kit" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="shipped-card">
            <h4>RAMP-Kit</h4>
            <p>Reversible Action Management Protocol. Govern decision velocity based on reversibility.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="https://github.com/synthanai/agentic-kit" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="shipped-card">
            <h4>Agentic-Kit</h4>
            <p>Reusable infrastructure for AI decision systems. Agents need infrastructure, not just prompts.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="https://github.com/synthanai/steal-kit" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="shipped-card">
            <h4>STEAL-Kit</h4>
            <p>Structured intelligence capture. Scan, Translate, Evaluate, Abstract, Leverage.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="https://github.com/synthanai/decision-moment-standard" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="shipped-card">
            <h4>Decision Moment Standard</h4>
            <p>The specification behind DMG. Decision governance as a protocol.</p>
          </a>
        </div>

        <h3 class="subsection-heading">Published Ebooks</h3>
        <div class="ebook-grid">
          <div class="work-item work-item--compact">
            <h4>PIC Your Profile</h4>
            <p class="work-type">Published</p>
            <p>Identity architecture ebook.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="work-item work-item--compact">
            <h4>21-Rep AI Gym</h4>
            <p class="work-type">Published</p>
            <p>AI capability building through structured reps.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="divider"><img src="/logo-h.svg" alt="ஃ" /></div>

      <!-- Mind: Cooking -->
      <section class="section--tight">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <span class="glow-dot" style="color: var(--mind-color);"></span>
          <h2>Mind <span class="layer-label">Cooking</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="work-item">
          <h3>Let's SPAR: Disagree to Agree</h3>
          <p class="work-type">Book · 21 Chapters · Publication-Ready</p>
          <p>How to argue with yourself productively. Structured dialectic thinking for better decisions, built on the SPAR protocol.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="work-item">
          <h3>Thirukkural: Mind, Body, Soul</h3>
          <p class="work-type">Book · In Active Writing</p>
          <p>Bridging 2000-year-old Tamil wisdom to modern leadership through the Mind-Body-Soul lens.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ebook-grid">
          <div class="work-item work-item--compact">
            <h4>SPAR Gracefully</h4>
            <p class="work-type">Ebook · Cooking</p>
            <p>SPAR methodology in practice.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="work-item work-item--compact">
            <h4>SURGE Your Clarity</h4>
            <p class="work-type">Ebook · Cooking</p>
            <p>Clarity through structured emergence.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cooking-repos">
          <p class="cooking-label">Also cooking on GitHub:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/synthanai/intent-of-thought-lifecycle" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Intent of Thought Lifecycle</a> — Extending the IoT paper into a living protocol</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/synthanai/student-kit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Student-Kit</a> — AI toolkit for students</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="divider"><img src="/logo-h.svg" alt="ஃ" /></div>

      <!-- Soul: Ideas & Concepts -->
      <section class="section--tight">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <span class="glow-dot" style="color: var(--soul-color);"></span>
          <h2>Soul <span class="layer-label">Ideas</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="soul-grid">
          <div class="soul-card">
            <h4>Living Systems</h4>
            <p>Organisations are not machines. They breathe, grow, decay. Every framework I build starts from this belief.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="soul-card">
            <h4>Structured Deliberation</h4>
            <p>Thinking is a craft. SPAR, RAMP, DMG: all exist because decisions deserve more friction, not less.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="soul-card">
            <h4>Tamil Wisdom Bridge</h4>
            <p>The Thirukkural is 2000 years old and speaks to modern leadership. Bridging ancient wisdom to contemporary practice.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="soul-card">
            <h4>AI with Intent</h4>
            <p>AI should declare its reasoning before generating. Transparency is not a feature, it is a requirement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <TamilRoot
        tamil="செயல்"
        transliteration="Seyal"
        meaning="Action, work, the doing. Not mere activity, but purposeful creation that leaves a mark."
        kural={`முடிவும் இடையூறும் முற்றியாங்கு எய்தும்\nபடுபயனும் பார்த்துச் செயல்.`}
        kuralNumber={676}
        kuralTranslation="Consider the end, the obstacles, and the benefit before acting."
      />
    </main>

    <Footer />

  </body>
</html>
